Package jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.unix

Defines a Java object model for the OVAL Unix components.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
DnsCacheItem The dnscache_item stores information retrieved from the DNS cache about a domain name, its time to live, and its corresponding IP addresses.
DnsCacheObject The dnscache_object is used by the dnscache_test to specify the domain name(s) that should be collected from the DNS cache on the local system.
DnsCacheState The dnscache_state contains three entities that are used to check the domain name, time to live, and IP addresses associated with the DNS cache entry.
DnsCacheTest The dnscache_test is used to check the time to live and IP addresses associated with a domain name.
EntityItemCapabilityType The EntityItemCapabilityType restricts a string value to a specific set of values that describe POSIX capability types associated with a process service.
EntityItemEncryptMethodType The EntityItemEncryptMethodType restricts a string value to a set that corresponds to the allowed encrypt methods used for protected passwords in a shadow file.
EntityItemEndpointType The EntityItemEndpointType restricts a string value to a specific set of values that describe endpoint types associated with an Internet service.
EntityItemGconfTypeType The EntityItemGconfTypeType restricts a string value to the seven values that specify the type of the value associated with a GConf preference key.
EntityItemInterfaceType The EntityItemInterfaceType restricts a string value to a specific set of values.
EntityItemRoutingTableFlagsType The EntityItemRoutingTableFlagsType restricts a string value to a specific set of values that describe the flags associated with a routing table entry.
EntityItemWaitStatusType The EntityItemWaitStatusType restricts a string value to two values, either wait or nowait, that specify whether the server that is invoked by inetd will take over the listening socket associated with the service, and whether once launched, inetd will wait for that server to exit, if ever, before it resumes listening for new service requests.
EntityItemXinetdTypeStatusType The EntityItemXinetdTypeStatusType restricts a string value to five values, either RPC, INTERNAL, UNLISTED, TCPMUX, or TCPMUXPLUS that specify the type of service registered in xinetd.
EntityStateCapabilityType The EntityStateCapabilityType restricts a string value to a specific set of values that describe POSIX capability types associated with a process service.
EntityStateEncryptMethodType The EntityStateEncryptMethodType restricts a string value to a set that corresponds to the allowed encrypt methods used for protected passwords in a shadow file.
EntityStateEndpointType The EntityStateWaitStatusType restricts a string value to two values, either wait or nowait, that specify whether the server that is invoked by inetd will take over the listening socket associated with the service, and whether once launched, inetd will wait for that server to exit, if ever, before it resumes listening for new service requests.
EntityStateGconfTypeType The EntityStateGconfTypeType restricts a string value to the seven values that specify the datatype of the value associated with a GConf preference key.
EntityStateInterfaceType The EntityStateInterfaceType restricts a string value to a specific set of values.
EntityStateRoutingTableFlagsType The EntityStateRoutingTableFlagsType restricts a string value to a specific set of values that describe the flags associated with a routing table entry.
EntityStateWaitStatusType The EntityStateEndpointType restricts a string value to a specific set of values that describe endpoint types associated with an Internet service.
EntityStateXinetdTypeStatusType The EntityStateXinetdTypeStatusType restricts a string value to five values, either RPC, INTERNAL, UNLISTED, TCPMUX, or TCPMUXPLUS that specify the type of service registered in xinetd.
FileBehaviors The FileBehaviors type defines a number of behaviors that allow a more detailed definition of the file_object being specified.
FileExtendedAttributeItem The file extended attribute item holds information about the individual file extended attributes found on a system.
FileExtendedAttributeObject The fileextendedattribute_object is used by a file extended attribute test to define the specific file(s) and attribute(s) to be evaluated.
FileExtendedAttributeState The fileextendedattribute_state element defines an extended attribute associated with a UNIX file.
FileExtendedAttributeTest The file extended attribute test is used to check extended attribute values associated with UNIX files, of the sort returned by the getfattr command or getxattr() system call.
FileItem The file item holds information about the individual files found on a system.
FileObject The file object is used by a file test to define the specific file(s) to be evaluated.
FileState The file state defines the different metadata associate with a UNIX file.
FileTest The file test is used to check metadata associated with UNIX files, of the sort returned by either an ls command, stat command or stat() system call.
GconfItem The gconf_item holds information about an individual GConf preference key found on a system.
GconfObject The gconf_object is used by a gconf_test to define the preference keys to collect and the sources from which to collect the preference keys.
GconfState The gconf_state element defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified GConf preference key.
GconfTest The gconf_test is used to check the attributes and value(s) associated with GConf preference keys.
InetdItem The file item holds information about the individual files found on a system.
InetdObject The inetd object is used by an inetd test to define the specific protocol-service to be evaluated.
InetdState The inetd state defines the different information associated with a specific Internet service.
InetdTest The inetd test is used to check information associated with different Internet services.
InterfaceItem The interface item enumerates various attributes about the network interfaces on a system.
InterfaceObject The interface object is used by an interface test to define the specific interfaces(s) to be evaluated.
InterfaceState The interface state enumerates the different properties associate with a Unix interface.
InterfaceTest The interface test enumerates various attributes about the interfaces on a system.
PasswordItem  
PasswordObject The password object is used by a password test to define the object to be evaluated.
PasswordState The password state defines the different information associated with the system passwords.
PasswordTest The password test is used to check metadata associated with the UNIX password file, of the sort returned by the passwd command.
Process58Item The file item holds information about the individual files found on a system.
Process58Object The process58 object is used by a process58 test to define the specific process(es) to be evaluated.
Process58State  
Process58Test The process58 test is used to check information found in the UNIX processes.
ProcessItem Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.8: Replaced by the process58 item.
ProcessObject Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.8: Replaced by the process58 object.
ProcessState Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.8: Replaced by the process58 state.
ProcessTest Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.8: Replaced by the process58 test.
RoutingTableItem The routingtable_item holds information about an individual routing table entry found in a system's primary routing table.
RoutingTableObject The routingtable_object is used by a routingtable_test to define the destination IP address(es), found in a system's primary routing table, to collect.
RoutingTableState The routingtable_state defines the different information that can be used to check an entry found in a system's primary routing table.
RoutingTableTest The routingtable_test is used to check information about the IPv4 and IPv6 routing table entries found in a system's primary routing table.
RunlevelItem The runlevel item holds information about the start or kill state of a specified service at a given runlevel.
RunlevelObject The runlevel object is used by a runlevel test to define the specific service(s)/runlevel combination to be evaluated.
RunlevelState The runlevel state holds information about whether a specific service is scheduled to start or stop at a given runlevel.
RunlevelTest The runlevel test is used to check information about which runlevel specified services are scheduled to exist at.
SccsItem Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: The Source Code Control System (SCCS) is obsolete.
SccsObject Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: The Source Code Control System (SCCS) is obsolete.
SccsState Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: The Source Code Control System (SCCS) is obsolete.
SccsTest Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: The Source Code Control System (SCCS) is obsolete.
ShadowItem  
ShadowObject The shadow object is used by a shadow test to define the shadow file to be evaluated.
ShadowState The shadows state defines the different information associated with the system shadow file.
ShadowTest The shadow test is used to check information from the /etc/shadow file for a specific user.
SysctlItem The sysctl_item stores information retrieved from the local system about a kernel parameter and its respective value(s).
SysctlObject The sysctl_object is used by a sysctl_test to define which kernel parameters on the local system should be collected.
SysctlState The sysctl_state contains two entities that are used to check the kernel parameter name and value(s).
SysctlTest The sysctl_test is used to check the values associated with the kernel parameters that are used by the local system.
Uname The Unix uname properties.
UnameItem Information about the hardware the machine is running on.
UnameObject The uname object is used by an uname test to define those objects to evaluated based on a specified state.
UnameState The uname state defines the information about the hardware the machine is running one.
UnameTest The uname test reveals information about the hardware the machine is running on.
XinetdItem The xinetd item holds information associated with different Internet services.
XinetdObject The xinetd object is used by an xinetd test to define the specific protocol-service to be evaluated.
XinetdState The xinetd state defines the different information associated with a specific Internet service.
XinetdTest The xinetd test is used to check information associated with different Internet services.
